30class TField : angle::NonCopyable
31{
32 public:
33 POOL_ALLOCATOR_NEW_DELETE
34 TField(TType *type, const ImmutableString &name, const TSourceLoc &line, SymbolType symbolType)
35 : mType(type), mName(name), mLine(line), mSymbolType(symbolType)
36 {
37 ASSERT(mSymbolType != SymbolType::Empty);
38 }
39
40 // TODO(alokp): We should only return const type.
41 // Fix it by tweaking grammar.
42 TType *type() { return mType; }
43 const TType *type() const { return mType; }
44 const ImmutableString &name() const { return mName; }
45 const TSourceLoc &line() const { return mLine; }
46 SymbolType symbolType() const { return mSymbolType; }
47
48 private:
49 TType *mType;
50 const ImmutableString mName;
51 const TSourceLoc mLine;
52 const SymbolType mSymbolType;
53};

92{
93 public:

96 explicit TType(TBasicType t, unsigned char ps = 1, unsigned char ss = 1);

196 bool isMatrix() const { return primarySize > 1 && secondarySize > 1; }
197 bool isNonSquareMatrix() const { return isMatrix() && primarySize != secondarySize; }

233 bool isVector() const { return primarySize > 1 && secondarySize == 1; }
234 bool isVectorArray() const { return primarySize > 1 && secondarySize == 1 && isArray(); }
235 bool isRank0() const { return primarySize == 1 && secondarySize == 1; }
236 bool isScalar() const
237 {
238 return primarySize == 1 && secondarySize == 1 && !mStructure && !isArray();
239 }
240 bool isScalarArray() const
241 {
242 return primarySize == 1 && secondarySize == 1 && !mStructure && isArray();
243 }
244 bool isScalarFloat() const { return isScalar() && type == EbtFloat; }
245 bool isScalarInt() const { return isScalar() && (type == EbtInt || type == EbtUInt); }

251 static constexpr char GetSizeMangledName(unsigned char primarySize, unsigned char secondarySize)
252 {
253 unsigned int sizeKey = (secondarySize - 1u) * 4u + primarySize - 1u;
254 if (sizeKey < 10u)
255 {
256 return static_cast<char>('0' + sizeKey);
257 }
258 return static_cast<char>('A' + sizeKey - 10);
259 }
260 const char *getMangledName() const;
261
262 bool sameNonArrayType(const TType &right) const;
263
264 // Returns true if arrayType is an array made of this type.
265 bool isElementTypeOf(const TType &arrayType) const;
266
267 bool operator==(const TType &right) const
268 {
269 size_t numArraySizesL = getNumArraySizes();
270 size_t numArraySizesR = right.getNumArraySizes();
271 bool arraySizesEqual = numArraySizesL == numArraySizesR &&
272 (numArraySizesL == 0 || mArraySizes == right.mArraySizes);
273 return type == right.type && primarySize == right.primarySize &&
274 secondarySize == right.secondarySize && arraySizesEqual &&
275 mStructure == right.mStructure;
276 // don't check the qualifier, it's not ever what's being sought after
277 }
278 bool operator!=(const TType &right) const { return !operator==(right); }
279 bool operator<(const TType &right) const
280 {
281 if (type != right.type)
282 return type < right.type;
283 if (primarySize != right.primarySize)
284 return primarySize < right.primarySize;
285 if (secondarySize != right.secondarySize)
286 return secondarySize < right.secondarySize;
287 size_t numArraySizesL = getNumArraySizes();
288 size_t numArraySizesR = right.getNumArraySizes();
289 if (numArraySizesL != numArraySizesR)
290 return numArraySizesL < numArraySizesR;
291 for (size_t i = 0; i < numArraySizesL; ++i)
292 {
293 if (mArraySizes[i] != right.mArraySizes[i])
294 return mArraySizes[i] < right.mArraySizes[i];
295 }
296 if (mStructure != right.mStructure)
297 return mStructure < right.mStructure;
298
299 return false;
300 }

309 // If this type is a struct, returns the deepest struct nesting of
310 // any field in the struct. For example:
311 // struct nesting1 {
312 // vec4 position;
313 // };
314 // struct nesting2 {
315 // nesting1 field1;
316 // vec4 field2;
317 // };
318 // For type "nesting2", this method would return 2 -- the number
319 // of structures through which indirection must occur to reach the
320 // deepest field (nesting2.field1.position).
321 int getDeepestStructNesting() const;

330 bool isStructSpecifier() const { return mIsStructSpecifier; }

332 // Return true if variables of this type should be replaced with an inline constant value if
333 // such is available. False will be returned in cases where output doesn't support
334 // TIntermConstantUnion nodes of the type, or if the type contains a lot of fields and creating
335 // several copies of it in the output code is undesirable for performance.
336 bool canReplaceWithConstantUnion() const;

339 void createSamplerSymbols(const ImmutableString &namePrefix,

348 bool isSampler() const { return IsSampler(type); }
349 bool isSamplerCube() const { return type == EbtSamplerCube; }
350 bool isAtomicCounter() const { return IsAtomicCounter(type); }
351 bool isSamplerVideoWEBGL() const { return type == EbtSamplerVideoWEBGL; }
352 bool isImage() const { return IsImage(type); }
353
354 private:
355 constexpr void invalidateMangledName() { mMangledName = nullptr; }
356 const char *buildMangledName() const;
357 constexpr void onArrayDimensionsChange(const TSpan<const unsigned int> &sizes)
358 {
359 mArraySizes = sizes;
360 invalidateMangledName();
361 }
362
363 TBasicType type;
364 TPrecision precision;
365 TQualifier qualifier;
366 bool invariant;
367 bool precise;
368
369 TMemoryQualifier memoryQualifier;
370 TLayoutQualifier layoutQualifier;
371 unsigned char primarySize; // size of vector or cols matrix
372 unsigned char secondarySize; // rows of a matrix
373
374 // Used to make an array type. Outermost array size is stored at the end of the vector. Having 0
375 // in this vector means an unsized array.
376 TSpan<const unsigned int> mArraySizes;
377 // Storage for mArraySizes, if any. This is usually the case, except for constexpr TTypes which
378 // only have a valid mArraySizes (with mArraySizesStorage being nullptr). Therefore, all
379 // modifications to array sizes happen on the storage (and if dimensions change, mArraySizes is
380 // also updated) and all reads are from mArraySizes.
381 TVector<unsigned int> *mArraySizesStorage;
382
383 // This is set only in the following two cases:
384 // 1) Represents an interface block.
385 // 2) Represents the member variable of an unnamed interface block.
386 // It's nullptr also for members of named interface blocks.
387 const TInterfaceBlock *mInterfaceBlock;
388
389 // nullptr unless this is a struct
390 const TStructure *mStructure;
391 bool mIsStructSpecifier;
392
393 mutable const char *mMangledName;
394};

396// TTypeSpecifierNonArray stores all of the necessary fields for type_specifier_nonarray from the
397// grammar
398struct TTypeSpecifierNonArray
399{
400 TBasicType type;
401 unsigned char primarySize; // size of vector or cols of matrix
402 unsigned char secondarySize; // rows of matrix
403 const TStructure *userDef;
404 TSourceLoc line;
405
406 // true if the type was defined by a struct specifier rather than a reference to a type name.
407 bool isStructSpecifier;
408
409 void initialize(TBasicType aType, const TSourceLoc &aLine)
410 {
411 ASSERT(aType != EbtStruct);
412 type = aType;
413 primarySize = 1;
414 secondarySize = 1;
415 userDef = nullptr;
416 line = aLine;
417 isStructSpecifier = false;
418 }
419
420 void initializeStruct(const TStructure *aUserDef,
421 bool aIsStructSpecifier,
422 const TSourceLoc &aLine)
423 {
424 type = EbtStruct;
425 primarySize = 1;
426 secondarySize = 1;
427 userDef = aUserDef;
428 line = aLine;
429 isStructSpecifier = aIsStructSpecifier;
430 }
431
432 void setAggregate(unsigned char size) { primarySize = size; }
433
434 void setMatrix(unsigned char columns, unsigned char rows)
435 {
436 ASSERT(columns > 1 && rows > 1 && columns <= 4 && rows <= 4);
437 primarySize = columns;
438 secondarySize = rows;
439 }
440
441 bool isMatrix() const { return primarySize > 1 && secondarySize > 1; }
442
443 bool isVector() const { return primarySize > 1 && secondarySize == 1; }
444};

446//
447// This is a workaround for a problem with the yacc stack, It can't have
448// types that it thinks have non-trivial constructors. It should
449// just be used while recognizing the grammar, not anything else. Pointers
450// could be used, but also trying to avoid lots of memory management overhead.
451//
452// Not as bad as it looks, there is no actual assumption that the fields
453// match up or are name the same or anything like that.
454//
455struct TPublicType
456{
457 // Must have a trivial default constructor since it is used in YYSTYPE.
458 TPublicType() = default;
459
460 void initialize(const TTypeSpecifierNonArray &typeSpecifier, TQualifier q);
461 void initializeBasicType(TBasicType basicType);
462
463 TBasicType getBasicType() const { return typeSpecifierNonArray.type; }
464 void setBasicType(TBasicType basicType) { typeSpecifierNonArray.type = basicType; }
465
466 unsigned char getPrimarySize() const { return typeSpecifierNonArray.primarySize; }
467 unsigned char getSecondarySize() const { return typeSpecifierNonArray.secondarySize; }
468
469 const TStructure *getUserDef() const { return typeSpecifierNonArray.userDef; }
470 const TSourceLoc &getLine() const { return typeSpecifierNonArray.line; }
471
472 bool isStructSpecifier() const { return typeSpecifierNonArray.isStructSpecifier; }
473
474 bool isStructureContainingArrays() const;
475 bool isStructureContainingType(TBasicType t) const;
476 void setArraySizes(TVector<unsigned int> *sizes);
477 bool isArray() const;
478 void clearArrayness();
479 bool isAggregate() const;
480
481 TTypeSpecifierNonArray typeSpecifierNonArray;
482 TLayoutQualifier layoutQualifier;
483 TMemoryQualifier memoryQualifier;
484 TQualifier qualifier;
485 bool invariant;
486 bool precise;
487 TPrecision precision;
488
489 // Either nullptr or empty in case the type is not an array. The last element is the outermost
490 // array size. Note that due to bison restrictions, copies of the public type created by the
491 // copy constructor share the same arraySizes pointer.
492 const TVector<unsigned int> *arraySizes;
493};
